<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Guide: Joining a Linux Device to Active Directory Domain Controller</h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Administrator access on the Linux device</li>
            <li>Network connectivity to the Domain Controller</li>
            <li>Required packages installed (details in script)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Steps to Join AD Domain</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Download the script</strong>
                <p>Choose one of the following scripts:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="#">Script.sh</a> (Standard implementation)</li>
                    <li><a href="#">Scripto.sh</a> (Alternative implementation with additional features)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Make the script executable</strong>
                <pre><code>chmod +x script.sh</code></pre>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Run the script</strong>
                <pre><code>./script.sh</code></pre>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Verification</strong>
                <p>After running the script, verify the domain join was successful:</p>
                <pre><code>id username@domain.com</code></pre>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
        <div class="warning">
            <p>If you encounter any issues during the process:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Check network connectivity to the domain controller</li>
                <li>Verify DNS settings are correctly configured</li>
                <li>Ensure hostname is properly set</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

